      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>To be aromatic, a molecule must have 4<i>n</i> + 2 <i>π</i> electrons and must have a planar, monocyclic system of conjugation. Cyclodecapentaene fulfills one of these criteria but not the other and has resisted all attempts at synthesis. Explain.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down-30\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBaDRWIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--b39dc271a1e1bb88f1811a8e01ebd0ad95aa9427/OChem_15_03_006.jpg\" alt=\"The ball-and-stick model shows a ten-membered ring with five alternate double bonds. The gray and black spheres represent hydrogen and carbon atoms, respectively.\">",
